---
import ServiceLayout from '@/layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';
import Container from '@/components/ui/Container.astro';
import SchemaFAQ from '@/components/seo/SchemaFAQ.astro';
---

<ServiceLayout
  title="Shower Remodeling"
  metaTitle="Shower Remodeling Seattle WA | Walk-In Showers & Custom Designs | Best KB Remodeling"
  metaDescription="Custom shower remodeling in Seattle. Walk-in showers, frameless glass, curbless designs, and luxury upgrades. Expert waterproofing and tile work. Free estimates!"
  slug="shower-remodeling"
  category="bathroom"
  heroImage="/images/service-shower-remodeling.jpg"
  features={[
    'Custom walk-in shower design and construction',
    'Frameless and semi-frameless glass enclosures',
    'Curbless / zero-threshold shower installations',
    'Rain showerheads, body jets, and handheld fixtures',
    'Built-in niches, corner shelves, and bench seating',
    'Complete waterproofing with membrane systems',
    'Steam shower system installation',
  ]}
>
  <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
    <p class="text-xl text-muted leading-relaxed mb-8">
      The shower is where most of us start and end our day, making it one of the most important spaces in your home. If you're replacing a worn-out tub-shower combo with a spacious walk-in design or upgrading to a spa-worthy steam shower, we create shower experiences that transform your daily routine. We've designed and built hundreds of custom showers across the Seattle metro, and we bring that expertise to every project.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Shower Design Options
    </h2>
    <p>
      Our most requested design is the walk-in shower, which replaces the traditional tub-shower combination to create an open, accessible bathing space. Walk-in showers can be configured with a low curb or completely curbless for a seamless transition from the bathroom floor. Curbless designs are particularly popular with Seattle homeowners who appreciate both the modern aesthetic and the practical accessibility benefits.
    </p>
    <p>
      For homeowners who want the ultimate bathing experience, we build steam showers — fully enclosed spaces with vapor-tight construction, a steam generator, and temperature controls that turn your shower into a personal steam room. Rain showerheads, thermostatic valve systems with body jets, and built-in Bluetooth speakers complete the luxury experience.
    </p>
    <p>
      We also specialize in shower-to-tub conversions and tub-to-shower conversions. If your household no longer needs a bathtub (or gains one), we handle the plumbing reconfiguration, waterproofing, and finishing with expert precision.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Glass Enclosures
    </h2>
    <p>
      The glass enclosure is the crowning detail of a custom shower. We install frameless, semi-frameless, and framed glass enclosures, with frameless being the most popular choice in contemporary Seattle homes. Frameless glass panels are made from 3/8" or 1/2" tempered safety glass and mounted with minimal hardware for a clean, unobstructed look that showcases your tile work.
    </p>
    <p>
      Glass options include clear, ultra-clear (low-iron for zero green tint), frosted, rain-textured, and patterned varieties. We also offer protective coatings like EnduroShield that repel water and mineral deposits, dramatically reducing cleaning frequency — a real benefit in Seattle where hard water spots are common.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Waterproofing: The Most Critical Step
    </h2>
    <p>
      A beautiful shower that leaks is a costly failure. That's why we treat waterproofing as the single most important element of every shower project. We use bonded waterproofing systems from Schluter (KERDI) or Laticrete (Hydro Ban) that create a continuous barrier behind and beneath the tile. Every seam, corner, and penetration receives additional membrane treatment.
    </p>
    <p>
      Before any tile is set, we flood-test every shower pan for 24 hours to verify watertight integrity. This test catches potential issues before they become expensive problems. Our attention to waterproofing is one reason we've never had a shower leak callback in our company's history — a record we're proud to maintain.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mt-12 mb-4">
      Functional Details That Matter
    </h2>
    <p>
      Beyond tile and glass, we focus on the functional elements that make your shower a pleasure to use. Built-in niches provide soap and shampoo storage without the need for hanging caddies. We recommend niche sizes of at least 12" x 24" and position them at a convenient height based on the users' stature. Corner seats and fold-down benches offer a comfortable perch for shaving legs or simply relaxing under the warm water.
    </p>
    <p>
      Linear drain systems offer both aesthetic and functional advantages over traditional center drains, allowing the entire floor to slope in one direction for cleaner large-format tile installations. Grab bars, strategically placed and finished to match your fixtures, add safety without compromising style — an important consideration for <a href="/services/aging-in-place/" class="text-accent hover:underline">aging-in-place</a> planning.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Cost Guide CTA -->
  <div class="bg-accent/5 border border-accent/20 rounded-2xl p-8 my-12">
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">How Much Does a Shower Remodel Cost?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Get detailed pricing breakdowns, budget tiers, and money-saving tips in our comprehensive cost guide.</p>
    <a href="/cost-guides/shower-remodel-cost/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-accent text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-accent-hover transition-colors">View Shower Remodel Cost Guide →</a>
  </div>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <Fragment slot="faq">
    <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white">
      <Container>
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-dark-text mb-10 text-center">
            Shower Remodeling FAQs
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                How much does a walk-in shower cost in Seattle?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                A custom walk-in shower in Seattle typically costs between $8,000 and $20,000, depending on size, tile selection, glass enclosure type, and fixture quality. A basic tub-to-shower conversion starts around $6,000, while a high-end steam shower with premium finishes can reach $25,000+. We provide detailed, transparent pricing for every project.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                Can you convert a bathtub to a walk-in shower?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                Yes, tub-to-shower conversions are one of our most popular projects. We remove the existing tub, reconfigure the drain and supply plumbing, build a properly waterproofed shower pan, install tile, and add a glass enclosure. The result is a more spacious, modern shower. We recommend keeping at least one tub in your home if you have young children or for resale considerations.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                What is a curbless shower and is it right for me?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                A curbless shower has no raised threshold at the entry — the bathroom floor flows directly into the shower floor with a gentle slope toward the drain. This creates a sleek, modern look and provides barrier-free access, which is great for accessibility. The floor structure may need to be modified to accommodate the drain slope, which we assess during your consultation.
              </div>
            </details>
            <details class="group bg-light rounded-xl border border-border">
              <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 font-semibold text-dark-text font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-lg">
                How long does a shower remodel take?
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-5 h-5 text-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" />
                </svg>
              </summary>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-muted leading-relaxed">
                A standard shower remodel takes 7-14 days from demolition to completion. This includes demolition (1 day), plumbing and framing (1-2 days), waterproofing (1 day plus cure time), tile installation (3-5 days), grouting and sealing (1 day), and glass enclosure installation (1 day). We coordinate the schedule to minimize the time your bathroom is out of commission.
              </div>
            </details>
          </div>
        </div>
      </Container>
    </section>
  </Fragment>

  <SchemaFAQ items={[
    { question: 'How much does a walk-in shower cost in Seattle?', answer: 'A custom walk-in shower in Seattle typically costs between $8,000 and $20,000, depending on size, tile selection, glass enclosure type, and fixture quality. A basic tub-to-shower conversion starts around $6,000, while a high-end steam shower with premium finishes can reach $25,000+. We provide detailed, transparent pricing for every project.' },
    { question: 'Can you convert a bathtub to a walk-in shower?', answer: 'Yes, tub-to-shower conversions are one of our most popular projects. We remove the existing tub, reconfigure the drain and supply plumbing, build a properly waterproofed shower pan, install tile, and add a glass enclosure. The result is a more spacious, modern shower. We recommend keeping at least one tub in your home if you have young children or for resale considerations.' },
    { question: 'What is a curbless shower and is it right for me?', answer: 'A curbless shower has no raised threshold at the entry — the bathroom floor flows directly into the shower floor with a gentle slope toward the drain. This creates a sleek, modern look and provides barrier-free access, which is great for accessibility. The floor structure may need to be modified to accommodate the drain slope, which we assess during your consultation.' },
    { question: 'How long does a shower remodel take?', answer: 'A standard shower remodel takes 7-14 days from demolition to completion. This includes demolition (1 day), plumbing and framing (1-2 days), waterproofing (1 day plus cure time), tile installation (3-5 days), grouting and sealing (1 day), and glass enclosure installation (1 day). We coordinate the schedule to minimize the time your bathroom is out of commission.' },
  ]} />
</ServiceLayout>
